    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-04-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-04-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="8"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d8">
                <head>8. Memorandum of Conversation<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d8fn1">Source:
                        National Archives, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files
                        1967–69, <gloss target="#t_POL1">POL</gloss>
                        <gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss>. Secret. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_SMJ1">Spear</persName> and approved in J on April 9. The
                        meeting was held in <persName>Johnson</persName>’s office. The memorandum is
                        part 6 of 6; parts 1 through 5 are ibid.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1969-04-01">April 1,
                            1969</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Meeting With The President</item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign</hi>
                    </item>
                    <item>Air Chief <persName corresp="#p_DCM1">Marshal Dawee
                        Chullasapya</persName>, Thai Minister of Communications <persName
                            corresp="#p_AP2">Arun Panupong</persName>, Thai Chargé d’Affaires</item>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">United States</hi>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">U. Alexis Johnson</persName>, Under Secretary
                        for Political Affairs</item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SMJ1">Moncrieff J. Spear</persName>, Country Director,
                        Thailand/Burma</item>
                </list>
                <p>Referring to his meeting with the President at the reception the previous
                        evening,<note n="2" xml:id="d8fn2">A memorandum of this conversation, March
                        31, is ibid.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_DCM1">Dawee</persName> said he had had a good talk. The
                    President has asked his views on Viet-Nam. He had replied that every day that
                    went by was a loss of time because American casualties continued to grow. He
                    also relayed a message from the Prime Minister that following the bombing halt
                    the situation in Southeast Asia had gotten worse. One way or another, we should
                    find a way to resume bombing in North Viet-Nam. <persName corresp="#p_DCM1"
                        >Dawee</persName> also felt that we should be prepared to use South Viet-Nam
                    ground forces to cut the infiltration. They were both capable and had the will
                    to do this job.</p>
            </div>
